<p id="fs-idp64846816"><span data-type="title">Check Your Learning</span>
Silicones are polymeric compounds containing, among others, the following types of covalent bonds: Si–O, Si–C, C–H, and C–C. Using the electronegativity values in <a class="autogenerated-content" href="#CNX_Chem_07_02_ENTable">Figure 7.6</a>, arrange the bonds in order of increasing polarity and designate the positive and negative atoms using the symbols δ+ and δ–.</p>
